<div class="recipe">
<p>Stir Fry is the ultimate weeknight dish. Once your ingredients are all prepped, the actual cooking process comes together incredibly quickly. Also, you can pack a ton of flavour into these types of dishes. You can tune this dish to your desired flavour, just add more sweet, spicy, or salty ingredients as you see fit. But, we recommend trying this recipe out with our ratios and going from there.</p>
<p>For this recipe, we will use your standard brick of ramen noodles that you can find in any store. However, you can use any noodles for this, even a spaghetti noodle! If you choose to a longer noodle, it is best to snap them in half first before boiling them.</p>
<p>To make the prep work even easier, you can buy <a href="https://amzn.to/3eR9qyh">*packages of vegetables already cut up for the use of coleslaw</a>. Obviously, we won't be using it for coleslaw, but these usually contain julliened carrots, cabbage, and brocolli - all things that go great in a dish like this!</p>
<p>To add more protein to this dish, feel free to add some chicken breast or ground meat. Just brown it off before adding the veggies to the pan and cut into bite-sized pieces.</p>
