<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <strong>Sauce:</strong>
    <ul>
        <li>1/2 cup hoisin sauce</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce (low sodium)</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon worcestershire sauce</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon cornstarch</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon sesame oil</li>
        <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper, crushed</li>
        <li>1 of the flavour packets included in the ramen packages (optional)</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>Stir Fry:</strong>
    <ul>
        <li>9 ounces ramen noodles (3 packages, or your preferred noodle)</li>
        <li>1-2 cups mixed veggies, shredded (cabbage, bell peppers, peas, bean sprouts and brocolli work great)</li>
        <li>2 carrots, peeled and jullienned</li>
        <li>3 teaspoons oil</li>
        <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon ginger, minced</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Whisk the sauce ingredients together and set aside. Make sure to whisk out any lumps from the cornstarch now.</li>
        <li>Cook your noodles to the package directions, drain and cool, while reserving some of the liquid.</li>
        <li>If you are adding meat to the dish, cook it now and set aside.</li>
        <li>To an oiled pan over medium high heat, add the oil and veggies. Cook for about 4 minutes, until tendercrisp (softened, but still has a snap to it). Add the ginger and garlic and cook until fragrent.</li>
        <li>Add the sauce to the pan and simmer until thickened, about 3 - 5 minutes. Add the meat back to the pan, if using.</li>
        <li>Add the cooked noodles to the pan, adding some of the reserved noodle water to achieve your desired consistency - remember that the sauce will thicken as it cools, so make it looser than you want now.</li>    
        <li>Top with your choice of garnish, such as green onions or sesame seeds. Enjoy!</li>
    </ol>
</div>
</div>





